in France long time ago; and about his little boy the dolphin, that\
would a been a king, but they took and shut him up in jail, and some say\
he died there.\
\
\'93Po\'92 little chap.\'94\
\
\'93But some says he got out and got away, and come to America.\'94\
\
\'93Dat\'92s good! \'a0But he\'92ll be pooty lonesome--dey ain\'92 no kings here, is\
dey, Huck?\'94\
\
\'93No.\'94\
\
\'93Den he cain\'92t git no situation. \'a0What he gwyne to do?\'94\
\
\'93Well, I don\'92t know. \'a0Some of them gets on the police, and some of them\
learns people how to talk French.\'94\
\
\'93Why, Huck, doan\'92 de French people talk de same way we does?\'94\
\
\'93_No_, Jim; you couldn\'92t understand a word they said--not a single word.\'94\
\
\'93Well, now, I be ding-busted! \'a0How do dat come?\'94\
\
\'93I don\'92t know; but it\'92s so. \'a0I got some of their jabber out of a book.\
S\'92pose a man was to come to you and say Polly-voo-franzy--what would you\
think?\'94\
\
\'93I wouldn\'92 think nuff\'92n; I\'92d take en bust him over de head--dat is, if he\
warn\'92t white. \'a0I wouldn\'92t \'91low no nigger to call me dat.\'94\
\
\'93Shucks, it ain\'92t calling you anything. \'a0It\'92s only saying, do you know\
how to talk French?\'94\
\
\'93Well, den, why couldn\'92t he _say_ it?\'94\
\
\'93Why, he _is_ a-saying it. \'a0That\'92s a Frenchman\'92s _way_ of saying it.\'94\
\
\'93Well, it\'92s a blame ridicklous way, en I doan\'92 want to hear no mo\'92 \'91bout\
it. \'a0Dey ain\'92 no sense in it.\'94\
\
\'93Looky here, Jim; does a cat talk like we do?\'94\
\
\'93No, a cat don\'92t.\'94\
\
\'93Well, does a cow?\'94\
\
\'93No, a cow don\'92t, nuther.\'94\
\
\'93Does a cat talk like a cow, or a cow talk like a cat?\'94\
\
\'93No, dey don\'92t.\'94\
\
\'93It\'92s natural and right for \'91em to talk different from each other, ain\'92t\
it?\'94\
\
\'93Course.\'94\
\
\'93And ain\'92t it natural and right for a cat and a cow to talk different\
from _us_?\'94\
\
\'93Why, mos\'92 sholy it is.\'94\
\
\'93Well, then, why ain\'92t it natural and right for a _Frenchman_ to talk\
different from us? \'a0You answer me that.\'94\
\
\'93Is a cat a man, Huck?\'94\
\
\'93No.\'94\
\
\'93Well, den, dey ain\'92t no sense in a cat talkin\'92 like a man. \'a0Is a cow a\
man?--er is a cow a cat?\'94\
\
\'93No, she ain\'92t either of them.\'94\
\
\'93Well, den, she ain\'92t got no business to talk like either one er the\
yuther of \'91em. \'a0Is a Frenchman a man?\'94\
\
\'93Yes.\'94\
\
\'93_Well_, den! \'a0Dad blame it, why doan\'92 he _talk_ like a man? \'a0You answer\
me _dat_!\'94\
\
I see it warn\'92t no use wasting words--you can\'92t learn a nigger to argue.\
So I quit.\
\
